# === CAT_CAS lab hygiene ===
# Patterns use **/ so they survive the track-folder reorganization.

# Build artifacts (regenerable: cargo build / python import)
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
**/target/
.pytest_cache/

# Large data blobs (>100 MB) kept in their owning experiment, gitignored,
# and documented as per-experiment requirements in docs/STORAGE.md:
#   - model weights (e.g. 16_catalytic_27b_inference/gemini_update/qwen_0.5b/)
#   - MERA .holo files (33_mera_compression)
#   - single-cell CSVs (46_phase_bio/.../cell_data/)
# The qwen_0.5b download is an external artifact: ignore the WHOLE dir (weights
# plus its config.json/tokenizer companions), not just the .safetensors, so it
# stays silent as it did before the track reorg. **/ keeps it depth-independent.
**/qwen_0.5b/
**/*.safetensors
**/*.holo
**/cell_data/
**/data/*.bin
**/data/*.mp4
**/telemetry/boundary_cloud_raw.csv
**/rust/mri_*.bin

# OS noise
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# NOTE: workspace/ holds a few tracked fixtures (exp 02/03) and is intentionally
# NOT ignored here; its regenerable BMP/artifacts are handled per-experiment.
